{
  "bookId": "heshanggong-laozi",
  "num": 32,
  "title": "第三十二章（聖德）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "道常無名，"
    },
    {
      "text": "樸雖小，天下莫能臣也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "侯王若能守之，萬物將自賓。"
    },
    {
      "text": "天地相合，以降甘露，"
    },
    {
      "text": "民莫之令而自均。"
    },
    {
      "text": "始制有名，"
    },
    {
      "text": "名亦既有，"
    },
    {
      "text": "夫亦將知之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "知之，所以不殆。"
    },
    {
      "text": "譬道之在天下，猶川谷之與江海。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道能陰能陽，能弛能張，能存能亡，故無常名也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道樸雖小，微妙無形，天下不敢有臣使道者也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "侯王若能守道無為，萬物將自賓，服從於德也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "侯王動作能與天相應和，天即降下甘露善瑞也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天降甘露善瑞，則萬物莫有教令之者，皆自均調若一也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "始，道也。有名，萬物也。 道無名能制於有名，無形，能制於有形也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "既，盡也。有名之物，盡有情欲，叛道離德，故身毀辱也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能法道行德，天亦將自知之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天知之，則神靈祐助，不復危怠。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "譬言道之在天下，與人相應和，如川谷與江海相流通也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
